article.headline: North Texas 77, New Mexico State 62
article.story: LAS CRUCES, N.M. (AP) -- The combination of desperation and inspiration was a winner for New Mexico State as the Aggies took their second straight game this season from North Texas. James Moore had 21 points, 11 rebounds and a school record eight blocks to lead the New Mexico State over the Mean Green 77-62 Saturday night. After trailing 33-30 at the half, the Aggies opened the second half with a 20-4 run led by Moore with 7 of those points and beat the Mean Green to almost every loose ball. Byron Davis capped the run with a 3-point play as the Aggies surged ahead 52-37 with 12:22 left. North Texas got no closer than 11 the rest of the way. "We played with a sense of urgency tonight," said Aggie coach Lou Henson. "I thought we out-hustled and it seemed like we played inspired basketball." The Aggies were coming off a 68-54 loss to Denver on Thursday. "We needed this win bad," said Moore, who moved into fifth place on the all-time scoring list for the Aggies. "It seems like every time we play well and win a game, we go out and play horrible in our next game. Hopefully, this will give us momentum as we go on the road again." Road games against New Orleans and South Alabama are up next. Davis, who had a career high 16 points, said North Texas' Shawnson Johnson was on the Aggies' minds after a much closer scrape with the Mean Green in Denton, Texas, last month. The final there was 70-67 in favor of NMSU, and Johnson was a major threat. "He killed us last time, but I think our defensive pressure got to him, and it gave us momentum," Davis said. Allen Haynes chipped in 14 for the Aggies. Leonard Hopkins had 22 points and eight boards for the Mean Green. Johnson added 13 points and five rebounds. "Both teams were urgent to win," said North Texas coach Johnny Jones. "They (the Aggies) just wanted it more. They hustled more and wanted it more. That's all there is to it." The Aggies (10-10, 4-5 Sun Belt) had 13 turnovers but outrebounded the Mean Green 45-43. North Texas (10-11, 5-4) started the game with a 6-0 run, then built a 17-10 lead with 12:30 left in the first half. But then the Aggies bounced back on a 7-0 run led by Moore, who scored 5. The Aggies hold a 19-5 series edge over the Mean Green.
